8 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Department of
Commerce; making appropriations; identifying sources;
9 stating purposes; providing for noncodification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
10 emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
15 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
16 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
17 Commerce from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
18 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
19 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
20 of Two Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($250,000.00) for the purpose
21 of providing resources to an economic development organization with
22 an office located in a town with a population of thirty-five
23 thousand (35,000) people or less per the latest Federal Decennial
24 Census, and located in the central part of the state, to construct
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4047 Page 1

1 and operate a transitional living facility to serve those aging out
2 of foster care or those who are low income.
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
4 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
5 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
6 Commerce from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
7 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
8 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
9 of Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000.00) for the purpose of
10 constructing needed facility upgrades, such as fairground arena
11 connectors, electrical infrastructure, and facilities associated
12 with livestock events at a location where statewide events commonly
13 referred to as a "state fair" occurs in the central region of the
14 state.
15 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
16 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
17 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
18 Commerce from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
19 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
20 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
21 of One Million Seven Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($1,750,000.00)
22 for the purpose of creating energy efficiencies at a university
23 campus located in Western Oklahoma with a student population of less
24 than one thousand one hundred (1,100) students.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4047 Page 2

1 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
2 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
3 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
4 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
5 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
6 Passed the House of Representatives the 14th day of April, 2026.
